_	Arguing that "because nature is a mess of riddles, we cannot expect revelation to be any clearer" obviously invited the retort that then both deism and Christianity were irrational.
_	He said: "It may be taunted with the retort that this is all Utopian and, therefore not worth a single thought...
_	In dialectic, this is countered by the retort that each totem or vahana, as an aspect of "ishta-devata" (or an "ishta-devata" or "asura" in its own right), has innumerable ineffable teachings, insights and spiritual wisdom; comparative analysis yields benefit, though knowledge and understanding is not served by collapsing their qualities into homogenous signification.
